## ReviewFlow Security Context

Keep these facts in mind when assessing severity:

### Auth Architecture
- Tokens are issued as **HTTP-only cookies**, not `Authorization` headers. Cookie flags (`Secure`, `SameSite`, `HttpOnly`, path scoping) are a primary attack surface.
- **Refresh cookie path** is scoped to auth paths (see `AuthCookieIssuer` / properties). A misconfigured path scope sends the refresh token on every request — widening the attack surface.
- **Token families (V28, V33)**: `refresh_token_families` + `session_contexts`. Reuse detection must revoke the entire family. A gap here = refresh token replay attack.
- **Step-up auth** at `/api/v1/auth/step-up` — must require a valid access token AND re-verify credentials. Must not be bypassable by a stale session.
- **Token version** (`token_version` column, V26) — incremented on password change / force logout. JWT filter must validate version on every request. A stale token with an old version must be rejected.
- **Lockout (V27)**: `failed_attempts` + `locked_until` on `users`. Must be enforced before password check, not after.
- **Password reset (V31)**: `password_reset_tokens` — must expire, must be single-use, must be invalidated on use.
- **`HASHIDS_SALT`** — must never be exposed. If leaked, all opaque IDs are reversible.

### Role Hierarchy
`SYSTEM_ADMIN > ADMIN > INSTRUCTOR > STUDENT`

Every privileged endpoint must check the minimum required role. `SYSTEM_ADMIN`-only endpoints must not be accessible by `ADMIN`. Role escalation paths must not exist.

### Known Configuration Sensitivities
- `JWT_SECRET`, `DB_PASSWORD`, `AWS keys`, `HASHIDS_SALT`, `MAIL_PASSWORD`, `ACTUATOR_INTERNAL_KEY` — must never appear in `/system/config` responses. Whitelist is `SystemService.SAFE_CONFIG_KEYS`.
- `clamav.enabled` defaults `false` locally — **must be `true` in `application-prod.properties`**. If prod profile doesn't force it on, malware uploads reach S3.
- `spring.jpa.open-in-view` — must be `false`. (Also flagged by the TX audit; flag here too as a security-adjacent concern.)

### What Is NOT in the Codebase
- **OAuth (PRD-14)** — not implemented. Do not flag missing OAuth security controls.
- **Content delivery (PRD-16)** — not implemented.

