## Per-File Assessment Checklist

Work through this internally before writing any finding:

```
[ ] Does it handle JWT issuance, validation, or cookies?        → S01, S02, S03
[ ] Does it touch refresh tokens or families?                   → S04
[ ] Does it implement or guard step-up?                        → S05
[ ] Does it implement login / failed attempt logic?            → S06
[ ] Does it implement password reset?                          → S07
[ ] Does it configure CORS or WebSocket origins?               → S08
[ ] Does it have @PreAuthorize or role checks?                 → S09
[ ] Does it return config / env data?                          → S10
[ ] Does it configure or guard actuator endpoints?             → S11
[ ] Does it configure or intercept WebSocket?                  → S12
[ ] Does it handle file uploads or call ClamAV?                → S13
[ ] Does it accept @RequestBody or @RequestParam?              → S14
[ ] Is it a high-frequency or auth-adjacent endpoint?          → S15
[ ] Does it load a resource by ID?                             → S16
[ ] Does it encode or validate a password?                     → S17
```

Do not flag unless the checklist produces a positive hit.

